A '''salt pan''' was a unit of measurement used by the [[Priapulin]]s. It was equal to 1.2 [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]]. It was thought that the unit was derived by their exploration of dried sea beds on [[Pria/Legends|Pria]].

